COVID Update
As of today we currently only have one student considered active and we have one teacher active. The teacher and student were wearing their mask while at school.
Both of these individuals have been quarantined most of last week and will continue to be quarantine for a total of 14 days.
We continue to clean the school extra daily and make sure all our staff are wearing mask or shields.
As a reminder, please do not send your child to school if they show any symptoms of Covid. We appreciate your support in helping to keep our kids safe.

We ask that you do not attempt to mention the name of the student or teacher in the comments below. If you have any questions you may contact the school.

post_text:
Dear Parents,

Student drop-off will be located in front of the flag pole next to the admin office. Students can then enter the cafeteria/gym for morning breakfast and assembly. Three Way ISD asks that you enter the school via CR 207 through the chain link gate located next to the white house. You will then exit through the pipe fence gate located directly in front of the school.

For student pickup at the end of the day, we ask that you enter the school in the same way, forming a line that begins directly in front of the admin office. Please remain in your vehicle moving up in the line as staff places children with the appropriate parent/guardian vehicle.

The map below should help assist you in understanding these procedures. Three Way ISD greatly appreciates your assistance in achieving our goal to keep all children safe.

Thank you,
Three Way ISD
text:
Dear Parents,

Student drop-off will be located in front of the flag pole next to the admin office. Students can then enter the cafeteria/gym for morning breakfast and assembly. Three Way ISD asks that you enter the school via CR 207 through the chain link gate located next to the white house. You will then exit through the pipe fence gate located directly in front of the school.

For student pickup at the end of the day, we ask that you enter the school in the same way, forming a line that begins directly in front of the admin office. Please remain in your vehicle moving up in the line as staff places children with the appropriate parent/guardian vehicle.

The map below should help assist you in understanding these procedures. Three Way ISD greatly appreciates your assistance in achieving our goal to keep all children safe.

Thank you,
Three Way ISD

post_text: There were only five recipients of the 2020 Rotary Club Leaders of Tomorrow grant. Students submitted an application with an essay explaining who their mentor is and why. The reasons why Imelda chose Mrs. Hilda Lorta are infinite. She has been a pillar in this community and school for many years! Imelda Yaneth Torres was selected as a recipient of the $1,000 grant, which will go toward her college expenses in the coming semesters. She is already a dual credit student at TWISD and has proven her determination and strong will to succeed at everything she puts her mind to. She is certainly a leader of tomorrow. Congratulations Imelda, and thank you, Mrs. Lorta for being a great mentor! “You can be anything you want to be. Dream big. Aim high. I’m very proud of you and I can’t wait to see what other accomplishments are ahead for you!” - Kayla Sparks, Principal

Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.

P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

shared_text:
The Flash Today - Erath County
May 18 at 4:30 PM ·

ATTENTION PARENTS OF LOCAL SCHOOL ATHLETES!
Our friends at Cross Timbers Ortho are offering UIL pre-participation physical exams for incoming 7th - 12th graders, Monday - Friday by appointment. Simply call 254-965-2663 to schedule an appointment and let them know your son/daughter needs a school physical and for which school.
There is no cost, as usual, but they do accept donations to your school's booster club, Foster's Home for Children, or canned food items donated to the local food bank. Pretty awesome deal, if you ask us!!!
Click the link below to print and complete forms before arrival.
Uiltexas.org/files/athletics/forms/PrePhysForm17-18.pdf
For more information, visit Crosstimbersortho.com/patient-resources or call the above number.

ISTATION INFORMATION:

In response to school closings due to COVID-19, ISIP Progress Monitoring at Home is now available for students at schools and districts using Istation's Indicators of Progress (ISIP) to assess and instruct students.

ISIP at Home will automatically assess students the first time they log in to Istation each month starting April 1. Students who were not assessed at school in March will take the ISIP Progress Monitoring at Home if they log in from home between March 22 and 31.

During school closings, educators can monitor progress while students use Istation at home. Data from ISIP Progress Monitoring at Home will be separated from ISIP data taken at school.

March 26 at 2:53 PM ·

Hey everyone! Mrs. Rucas here!

I am working on few yearbook pages that I need your help with!
It's your turn to be the photographer! Here is what I'm looking for:

1) Corona Virus Check
Send me pics of you playing board games, couch surfing, dog walking, hobbies and family time!

2) Pets
Our furry friends have benefitted more than anyone from the current state of the world. Please share photos, whether they are cute images, animal mischief or selfies.

3) Snacks
Being at home means we’re raiding the kitchen cabinets a lot more frequently. What are your go-to foods?

You can send pictures via facebook messenger or email me at crucas@twisd.us!

post_text: Broiler show and Rabbit show at county stock show
text: Broiler show and Rabbit show at county stock show

post_text:
We asked 14 students that did not have an animal project entered in the county show to come and assist their classmates with showing chickens (since a pen is made of 3 chickens, it takes 3 people per pen to show). When the County Extension agent said she needed extra hands in the show ring before our students were all helping each other, they didn’t think twice before coming forward and helping all of the other kids out. Our students showed chickens for people they had never met before, which meant getting pecked, hit with wings, scratched, and maybe even pooped on. No, maybe we don’t have everything a big school can offer, but I guarantee what we do have is much more valuable. Watching our students flood that show ring today just to help others out made my heart smile, and it reminded me once again why I am proud to be a Brave!
Today was just the show for chickens and rabbits. Much more to come over the next couple of days. Wish these exhibitors well as they showcase their hard work!

post_text:
THIS is how we do Christmas at Three Way! ✔️Cultural lunch with all kinds of different foods ✔️students going to the nursing home and having real, genuine conversations with residents
✔️high school students decorating their “home” (the whole high school) with tons of decorations and a real live Christmas tree
✔️students from all grade levels going to the high school to enjoy the Christmas spirit and have older kids read to them, sing with them, and dance with them
✔️book exchange parties with hot chocolate and cookie decorating contests
✔️making special gifts for our loved ones using our STEM skills
✔️laughter, love, FAMILY time
We are proud to be Braves today and every day!

shared_text:
Three Way Technology & Engineering is at Three Way ISD.
March 1, 2019 at 2:54 PM · Stephenville, TX ·

Our plane projects are fun and engaging - students have taken ownership and are passionate about what they have built. Building the planes, our students have learned how-to:

+ Read engineering drawings.
+ Identify different types of wood and their applications.
+ Understand different adhesives and applications.
+ Use different tools: saws, calipers, sander, grinder, drills.
+ Measure angle relationships: polyhedral and dihedral angles.
+ Install equipment: electric motors, servos, control rods & control horns.
+ Solder & build wiring harnesses.
+ Program radio transmitter: adjust sub trim, servo reversing, travel adjustment.
+ Calculate longitudinal stability and aerodynamic chord.
+ Measure electric motor power output in watts.
+ Apply heat shrink covering to the aircraft structures.

+ TEAMWORK - working together and everyone doing the part.
+ PERSISTENCE - never giving up.
+ FAITH - faith in engineering principles.
+ GRIT - digging down deep and pushing forward.

....& CONFLICT RESOLUTION.

WE ARE PROUD OF OUR STUDENTS!!!

Three Way ISD
Paul Ryan

post_text:
We are so excited about the new year. There are some new faces on staff and many new students. We still have room in several grades.
With the addition of another Kindergarten teacher we have room for sure but several other grades as well.
We have plenty of room for 9th and 10th. Don’t miss out on the new programs and new building.
Come on out next week and register.

TWO-A-DAYS WITH THE BRAVES -- This is the first year for the Three Way High School Braves to play a varsity schedule and head coach Troy Sparks and the Braves have been out getting ready for the upcoming season all week! The Flash Today's JESSIE HORTON caught up with them this morning and got LOTS OF GREAT SNAPS. We've posted TONS MORE on our website here: http://theflashtoday.com/?p=81286
